582
00:29:26,150 --> 00:29:27,710
So, there's no such thing as time.

583
00:29:28,700 --> 00:29:29,950
I'm even more confused now.

584
00:29:31,160 --> 00:29:32,510
Let me put it more simply.

585
00:29:32,790 --> 00:29:34,150
The essence of time

586
00:29:34,150 --> 00:29:35,540
is just a consensus

587
00:29:35,540 --> 00:29:37,110
made by all beings in the world,

588
00:29:37,110 --> 00:29:38,230
a common agreement

589
00:29:38,230 --> 00:29:39,470
for coordinated labor.

590
00:29:39,990 --> 00:29:40,750
A day

591
00:29:40,750 --> 00:29:42,310
can be divided into 12 periods,

592
00:29:42,310 --> 00:29:43,750
but it can also be divided

593
00:29:43,750 --> 00:29:45,190
into 24, 48,

594
00:29:45,190 --> 00:29:46,230
or even countless ones.

595
00:29:46,230 --> 00:29:47,630
As long as everyone in the world accepts it,

596
00:29:47,630 --> 00:29:48,590
the number of divisions

597
00:29:48,590 --> 00:29:49,750
doesn't really matter.

598
00:29:49,990 --> 00:29:51,510
In fact, time has never changed.

599
00:29:51,510 --> 00:29:52,510
What we can truly possess

600
00:29:52,510 --> 00:29:53,870
is only one time,

601
00:29:54,190 --> 00:29:55,180
